Notes: The 'row_id' represents a unique identifier for each measurement record. Path 32 provides a direct identifier for Measurement, which is semantically appropriate and straightforward.

The patient_id corresponds to an identifier for the patient linked to the measurement. Path 26 via hasPatient to PatientIdentifier semantically matches the patient_id column better than the direct patient resource.

Measurement_code maps naturally to the hasCode property of Measurement pointing to a Code entity. Although 2-hop paths exist to Terminology (path 5), the code itself is the core concept represented here.

Measurement_value corresponds to the numeric or string value of the measurement quantity. The 2-hop path via hasQuantity to hasValue (string datatype) fits best given example values are decimal numbers represented as strings.
Measurement_unit describes the unit of the measured quantity and thus maps to the hasUnit property of Quantity, which is the natural semantic representation for units.

Measurement_date corresponds to when the measurement was taken, matching the hasMeasurementDateTime property of Measurement with xsd:dateTime datatype. This path is more precise than generic hasDateTime (path 18).
